    <text id="F8005T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McClure accepts Cameron's explaination of his rumored opposition to McClure and
                    seeks common ground on the big issues of the day.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
              

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1858-11-01"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 1st</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr</abbr> Sir-</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of the 30th ult. is at hand. It is what I felt that I deserved at your
                    hands, and what I expected. I was unwilling to regard you as pursuing a cause of
                    decided hostility to me, without affording you an opportunity of being heard;
                    and I am free to say that the position indicated in your letter is fully
                    satisfactory. Set it therefore <unclear>pass</unclear></p>
                <p>I concur with you as to the duty of the next<pb n="2"/>legislature. I shall go
                    for a short <unclear>reprieve</unclear>, for harmonious action-ever keeping in
                        <unclear>view</unclear> the important struggle just approaching, in which
                    Pennsylvania <hi rend="underline">must</hi> be true to herself.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">AKMcClure</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <abbr expan="General">Genl</abbr>
                        <unclear>Slearmerson</unclear>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
